article.description: — Josh Caldwell had a career-high 20 points as Army topped Holy Cross 83-68 on Saturday.
article.headline: Caldwell scores 20 to lift Army over Holy Cross 83-68
article.linkText: Caldwell scores 20 to lift Army over Holy Cross 83-68
article.story: WORCESTER, Mass. -- — Josh Caldwell had a career-high 20 points as Army topped Holy Cross 83-68 on Saturday. Alex King had 19 points for Army (6-2, 2-1 Patriot League). Lonnie Grayson added 12 points. Tucker Blackwell had 11 points. Austin Butler had 16 points and nine rebounds for the Crusaders (1-2, 1-2). Ryan Wade added 14 points. Gerrale Gates had 13 points and eight rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
